. This gap has been filled now by this work. Sebastian Brock’s Foreword gives important information on the background and authenticity of the different sources that form the basis of the text. This biography is unique in that it brings together some very early accounts of the birth of Mary, the birth of Jesus, the flight into Egypt, and most importantly, the very rare account of the ‘Dormition’ or ‘falling asleep’ of the Blessed Mother.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aApocryphal books (New Testament) 0aApocryphal books (New Testament). 0aManuscripts, Medieval. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Literature & the Arts.2bisacsh1 aBrock, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnight, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074330240uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324356240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463243562423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463243562/original  a978-3-11-074330-2  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK